Subject: XSS Vulnerabilities in MintBoard

Information
--------------------
Name :  XSS Vulnerabilities in MintBoard
Software :  MintBoard 0.3 and possibly below.
Vendor Homepage :  http://www.mintboard.com
Vulnerability Type :  Cross-Site Scripting
Severity :  Medium
Researcher :  Canberk Bolat
Advisory Reference :  NS-13-001

Description
--------------------
Mintboard is a forum software who aims to do less and do it better. An
attempt to say goodbye to the bloat found in forum software.

Details
--------------------
MintBoard is affected by XSS vulnerabilities in version 0.3.
http://example.com/?login=3 (POST: name)
http://example.com/?login=3 (POST: pass)
http://example.com/?signup=3 (POST: name)
http://example.com/?signup=3 (POST: pass)

You can read the full article about Cross-Site Scripting and SQL Injection
vulnerabilities from here:

Cross-site Scripting (XSS):
https://www.mavitunasecurity.com/xss-vulnerabilities-in-mintboard/

